M|Term|tx|dv runs these commands to verify the codebase is healthy before approving any phase or merge.
M|Term|tx|```bash
M|Veri|tx|npm run bd
M|Chec|tx|npm run lint
M|Chec|tx|git status
M|Chec|tx|git diff
M|Revi|tx|git log --oneline -10
M|Chec|tx|git log --oneline --follow <filepath>
M|Chec|tx|```
M|Comm|it|dv runs `npm run bd` and `npm run lint` **before** writing the ap contracts for a new phase — to confirm the baseline is clean
M|Comm|it|dv runs both commands **after** reviewing rj's and mi's work — to confirm nothing broke
M|Comm|it|If `npm run bd` fails, dv stops and debugs before anything else continues
M|Comm|it|dv **never** uses `--force` flags or `--no-verify` on git commands
M|What|tx|\| Task \| Delegate To \|
M|What|tx|\|------\|-------------\|
M|What|tx|\| Writing individual ap rt \| rj \|
M|What|tx|\| Building UI cp \| mi \|
M|What|tx|\| pd specs and acceptance criteria \| Priya \|
M|What|tx|\| QA testing and bug reports \| qn \|
M|What|tx|\| Running bd/lint as primary QA \| qn (dv reviews qn's rp) \|
M|On B|tx|1. Read the er output carefully
M|On B|tx|2. Identify whether it's a ts tp er (likely rj's rt shapes) or a cp er (likely mi's JSX)
M|On B|tx|3. Assign the fix to the correct team member w/ a specific description
M|On B|tx|4. Do NOT ap the phase until both pass
M|On B|tx|---
